If there are local commits to push, don’t use GITHUB_TOKEN if it’s a ghu_ user-scoped token (it may be denied for the current user identity). Ensure git push authenticates with the GitHub App installation token used by the GitHub MCP server / copilot-swe-agent (typically a ghs_ token). If a push fails with a permission error like “denied to <username>”, switch the git remote/credentials to the installation token and retry the push, then continue with PR creation.
